Citation.sAbstract: The paper presents ninety-six PvTx vapor phase data for binary blends of 2,3,3,3- tetrafluoroprop-1-ene (R1234yf) and isobutane (R600a) and one hundred-two PvTx vapor phase data for binary blends of trans-1,3,3,3-tetrafluoroprop-1-ene (R1234ze(E)) and R600a. The R1234yf/R600a blends were measured for five isochores (0.080, 0.094, 0.128, 0.166, 0.170) m3*kg-1 for (303 less than T less than 383) K for six R600a mole fractions (0.234, 0.400, 0.472, 0.606, 0.772, 0.850) mol*mol-1. The R1234ze(E)/R600a blends were measured for four isochores (0.085, 0.090, 0.101, 0.106) m3*kg-1 for (303 less than T less than 383) K for six R600a mole fractions (0.290, 0.428, 0.516, 0.612, 0.685, 0.755) mol*mol-1. The data were fitted with a Fundamental Helmoltz Equation of State (EoS), a Peng-Robinson EoS, and a truncated Virial EoS.
Citation.sTitle: Vapor Phase PTx Measurements of Binary Blends of 2,3,3,3-Tetrafluoroprop-1-ene + Isobutane and trans-1,3,3,3-Tetrafluoroprop-1-ene + Isobutane
